\f3\i\b \cf4 \cb3 Addition of HCN to propanone\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0\b0 \cf4 \cb3 In the first stage, there is a nucleophilic attack by the cyanide ion on the slightly positive carbon atom in C=O.\
\
The negative ion formed then picks up a hydrogen ion from a hydrogen cyanide molecule, to form 2-hydroxy-2-methylpropanenitrile.\
\
